President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Finch Fulton as the Assistant Secretary of Transportation (Transportation Policy) and David A. Wright as a Member of the Nuclear Regulatory Commission. Fulton has previously worked on transportation and infrastructure policy and served as a Special Advisor to the Secretary on Transportation Policy. Wright has experience as an energy and water consultant and policy advisor on nuclear waste issues, and has served as the President of the National Association of Regulatory Utility Commissioners. Trump also announced his intent to appoint Michael Lucci as a Member to the Federal Service Impasses Panel and appoint several individuals to key positions in the Commission of Fine Arts and the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences.